@scp54 I obviously got that wrong then as I thought I got it from you -Sorry -when did they stop?

Galle made simpler # 26: Dating : Establishments Galle needed to bring something special to the 1925 Paris Exhibition - they developed a series of metal-mould blown cameo vase -very difficult to make -they only just got them in time for the show and production stopped in 1928 https://t.co/KP6VpOZhGn

Galle made simpler # 25: Dating : in the Late 20s Galle often produced high quality large 'exhibition' pieces celebrating things like the new discoveries in Egypt and solo flight across the world  -most of these are now in Museum https://t.co/mOjxaMsGpg

Galle made simpler # 24: Dating : in the Late 1920s some new colours started appearing. Galle Cameo vases started having more pastel and semi opaque background colours- Although some later period Galle is inferior -these are super quality and quite rare https://t.co/U0k1T2e2hj

Galle made simpler # 23: Dates post WW1 was the biggest period of production for Galle cameo - some inferior quality was made, but so too some superb pieces -We see the first signs of Art Deco starting appearing in their style https://t.co/fJYxo3wEv5

Galle made simpler # 22: Dating : One of the most distinctive periods of Galle Cameo production was during WW1 -early in the war glass production ceased, but the furnaces ran brief in Early 1917 making a limited range of two colour vases, mostly seaweeds -very rare & distinctive https://t.co/ggur0zLdXq

Galle made simpler # 21: Dates - the first Emile Galle Cameo vases c1900-1905  that looked like the pieces we all know, were often on shapes that has been designed for the enamels - so they where sometimes quite oddly shaped https://t.co/hEFU0FiVou

Galle made simpler # 20: Dates - around 1889 Saw some of the earliest Galle cameos in the more modestly priced ranges - shown at the Paris exhibition - often a had very chinoiserie in look https://t.co/pPX6V0mLuY

Galle made simpler # 18: Dates: -it's really quite hard to date Emile Galle Cameos accurately, but there are certain distinctive looks that are easier to date -The earliest Galle 1880-1896 glass was either major exhibition pieces and, for the more modest pockets, enamels https://t.co/QRjvwqJH7o

Galle made simpler # 17: Colours : Multiple colours -one of the defining factors of the value of a Emile Galle Cameo vase is the number of layers/colours - 1 and 2 colours are common - 3 is unusual, 4 is special - more than that is quite rare -here are a selection https://t.co/39QJP2mm1u

Galle made simpler # 16: Colours : Purple -Like orange one of the most common Emile Galle cameo colours- often on clear or over yellow -rarely, like the last example below, polished behind to remove the yellow behind to make the purple more vibrant https://t.co/cpgh3dxN9H
Galle made simpler # 15: Colours : Pink -one of Emile Galle's least used colours -often used to contrast purple or in amongst multiple other colours https://t.co/8hM7zgkRO9

Galle made simpler # 14: Colours : Orange -orange on clear is one of Galle's most common colour combinations but he also used it in more complex mixes with pinks and greens (third example) https://t.co/FPiHicZSLQ

Galle made simpler # 13: Colours : Greens -oddly Green is one of Galle's least used colours in Cameo  -and even then he often used blue over yellow to get green (last example) -rather than using green glass (first three) https://t.co/6dQfTV0zlB

Galle made simpler # 12: Colours : Browns -  Galle's cameo browns are usually top layers and can range from intense brown to just a ghostly hint of brown -ideal for plants and flowers- depending on the lower layers in can vary greatly in impact https://t.co/mXS6LxMqNp

Galle made simpler # 11: Blues - most often combined with purple and quite often over yellow probably his most popular cameo colour combination -in the best pieces the yellow is polished out from behind the blue to make the flowers look more vibrant (left hand pair below) https://t.co/1ck1cIWvSs

Galle made simpler # 10: Colours -Amazingly Emile Galle spent years developing his own colour range - most glass makers just buy their colours in. Although similar to other's colours Galle's are unique -and so was the way he combined them - here are some reds with orange. https://t.co/b5YlVBoE5S

Galle made simpler # 9 Galle cameos come in a wide variety of shapes, maybe 1000s, but each one is distinctive -making fakes easier to spot - if the shape isn't quite right then the piece is probably wrong! Here are a few unusual shapes https://t.co/nUR3g3DVJO

Galle made simpler # 8 Shapes and sizes -one of the most popular Galle cameo shapes with collectors is the Banjo -it comes in 2 sizes and possibly has the widest range of patterns of any shape -also as it is a distinctive shape its easy to see if there has been any hidden damage https://t.co/G4mdxRMJFj

Galle made simpler # 7: Shapes and sizes. Galle made a very wide range of shapes and sizes from giant to tiny -here is one of the larger next to a miniature -often people remove chips from Galle with polishing and that affects the shape -learning the original shapes is important. https://t.co/BenbyhjuNc

Now cancelled my order with Mountain Warehouse, no problem with them just that Hermes Parcels appear to not like actually delivering items. Sad for a good company like MW to have to put up with goods being cancelled because of other companies appalling service.
Read on a Twitter a couple of days ago that Hermes Parcels has the lowest rating out of all the couriers, two star. After my experience with them I would say that is excessively high.

Strange that it’s hard to phone Hermes Parcels, could it be that they don’t want to hear all the customers complaints. Still waiting for my parcel that apparently was delivered last night, also very strange cctv doesn’t show it was delivered.

Typical Hermes, receive message saying parcel will be delivered between 2 &4 at 9.04pm get another saying it has been delivered which it wasn’t. What a dreadful service and what a deliberate lie. Mountain Warehouse I would suggest you use a different courier.

The first Amish settlement in Crittenden County was established in 1977. At present the Amish population has grown to almost 400 residents. #amish #marionky

Visiting the #Amish in Crittenden County is like taking a step back in time. They have no telephones or electricity and use horses and buggies for transportation. When you visit, you will see their meticulous care of the land, their craftsmanship in cabinet and furniture making!
May this festive season sparkle and shine, may all of your wishes and dreams come true, and may you feel this happiness all year round. Merry Christmas! #christmas
The City of Marion, Kentucky is the county seat of Crittenden County. Located south of the Ohio River and north east of Land Between the Lakes National Wildlife Area. #visitmarion
Marion is known for its friendly southern hospitality and small town charm. #visitmarion #explore

Located at 113 Sturgis Road, the "Dip". The menu may read like a fast food restaurant, but each item is grilled fresh as you order. It may take a little longer than the local drive through, but the first bite tells you it was well worth the wait. #marionky
